      "source_kind": "source-snippet",
      "source_repo": "Polly-Contrib/Simmy",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "Simmy is a [chaos-engineering](http://principlesofchaos.org/) and fault-injection tool, integrating with the [Polly resilience project for .NET](https://github.com/App-vNext/Polly). It is releasing April 2019 and works with [Polly v7.0.0](https://www.nuget.org/packages/Polly/7.1\u2026"
    },
    {
      "source_kind": "repo-description",
      "source_repo": "bjartnes/hikke",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "A k6/.NET red/green load testing workshop"
    },
    {
      "source_kind": "source-snippet",
      "source_repo": "bjartnes/hikke",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "This repository is for a workshop to understand how to introduce and deal with a bounded disturbance."
    },
    {
      "source_kind": "repo-description",
      "source_repo": "vany0114/chaos-injection-using-simmy",
      "status": "candidate-context",
      "text": "A microservice based application to demonstrate how chaos engineering works with Simmy using chaos policies in a distributed system."
